<section class="section section--bg-soft">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <h2 style="text-align: center;">Frequently asked.</h2>
    <div class="faq">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">How and when is payment handled?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>After the route is agreed and the price confirmed, before the car is dispatched. PIX, bank transfer, cash and cards. Regular partners and companies — invoicing with post-trip payment.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">What happens if my flight is delayed?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>We track the flight via the number you share at booking. The pickup is adjusted automatically to the new ETA, without a "waiting fee".</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">Can I cancel or change a trip?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>Free changes and cancellation more than 24 hours before pickup. 24–6 hours: partial preparation fee. Less than 6 hours: pickup is charged.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">What is included in the price?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>Driver, fuel, tolls and parking along the route. Extra stops or waiting time are agreed in advance, never added on the road.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">Do you operate at night and on weekends?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>Yes, without breaks. Night and weekend trips are not "special tariff" — but they need more lead time, so reach out as early as you can.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

